{
  "esm": "0.4.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "flux_interp_15",
    "description": "Actinic flux interpolation function for Fast-JX wavelength bin 15 (316 nm). Migrated from GasChem.jl src/interpolations_FastJX.jl:36-53 (`flux_interp_15(P, csa)`, @register_symbolic). Each function performs a bilinear interpolation of the precomputed tropospheric actinic flux table Z_all[15] (23 pressure levels \u00d7 61 cosSZA values) using the interp.bilinear primitive. The gt-p3ep (@register_symbolic) gap is resolved by expressing the lookup as an AST composition of the closed interp.bilinear primitive.",
    "tags": [
      "gaschem",
      "fast-jx",
      "photolysis",
      "registered_function",
      "actinic_flux",
      "wavelength_bin_15",
      "interp-bilinear"
    ],
    "created": "2026-05-22T00:00:00Z",
    "authors": [
      "GasChem.jl contributors",
      "EarthSciModels migration (esm-9vcj)"
    ],
    "references": [
      {
        "citation": "Neu, J.L., Prather, M.J., and Penner, J.E. (2007), Global atmospheric chemistry: Integrating over fractional cloud cover, J. Geophys. Res., 112, D11306, doi:10.1029/2006JD008007. \u2014 Source for the Fast-JX scheme."
      },
      {
        "citation": "Source: GasChem.jl/src/interpolations_FastJX.jl (commit 8c12c048482b515fb8eb2110bf8ab4b4f4e71309). flux_interp_15(P, csa) is the @register_symbolic wrapper for the bilinear interpolator over Z_all[15] (tropospheric actinic flux table, wavelength bin 316 nm)."
      }
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "flux_interp_15": {
      "reference": {
        "notes": "source_ref: GasChem.jl@8c12c048482b515fb8eb2110bf8ab4b4f4e71309:src/interpolations_FastJX.jl:36-53\n\nUpstream definition:\n  flux_interp_15(P, csa) = interpolations_18_const[15](ustrip(P), ustrip(csa))\n  @register_symbolic flux_interp_15(P, csa)\n\nwhere interpolations_18_const[15] is:\n  extrapolate(Interpolations.scale(\n      interpolate(Z_all[15], BSpline(Linear()), OnGrid()),\n      tropospheric_P, cosSZA_vals), Flat())\n\nLoaded from: src/tropospheric_interpolation_data.bson\n  Z_all: vector of 18 matrices (23\u00d761 each = 23 P \u00d7 61 cosSZA)\n  tropospheric_P: 23 pressure values [1000..100000] Pa\n  cosSZA_vals: 61 cos(SZA) values [-0.2..1.0]\n\nThe @register_symbolic gap (gt-p3ep) is resolved by composing the closed function registry: interp.bilinear over the precomputed table.\n\nJulia column-major serialization note: Z_all[15] in Julia is a 23\u00d761 matrix indexed as [P_idx, cosSZA_idx]. JSON.jl serializes this column-major as a 61\u00d723 array (cosSZA is the outer dimension, P is the inner). The interp.bilinear call therefore uses (cosSZA_axis, P_axis) as axes in that order.\n\nWavelength bin 15: 316 nm (Fast-JX WL array index 15).\n\nExtrapolation: flat (Flat()) \u2014 matches Interpolations.jl upstream."
      },
      "tolerance": {
        "rel": 1e-09,
        "abs": 1e-30
      },
      "variables": {
        "P": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "Pa",
          "default": 101325.0,
          "description": "Air pressure (Pa). One axis of the bilinear actinic-flux table."
        },
        "csa": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "1",
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Cosine of the solar zenith angle (dimensionless, clipped to [-0.2, 1.0] with flat extrapolation)."
        },
